UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1218
1 AN ACT relating to juvenile justice, making an appropriation therefor, and
2 declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 15A IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) There is hereby created in the Department of Juvenile Justice a trust and agency
7 account to be known as the juvenile services fund. The fund shall consist of
8 moneys received from state appropriations, gifts, grants, and federal funds.
9 (2) The fund shall be administered by the Department of Juvenile Justice.
10 (3) Amounts deposited in the fund shall be used for:
11 (a) Delinquency prevention and early intervention services for youths;
12 (b) Providing individualized, community-based wraparound services for justice-
13 involved youths and their families;
14 (c) Alternatives to detention; and
15 (d) Re-entry programs and facilities.
16 (4) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, fund amounts not expended at the close of a fiscal
17 year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the next fiscal year.
18 (5) The Department of Juvenile Justice shall provide a report on or before September
19 30 of each year to the Legislative Research Commission for referral to the
20 Interim Joint Committee on Judiciary, detailing:
21 (a) The total amount of funds from the juvenile services fund disbursed since
22 the last reporting period;
23 (b) A list of each organization awarded funding from the juvenile services fund
24 during the reporting period;
25 (c) The type of service each organization awarded funding during the reporting
26 period intends to deliver;
27 (d) The total amount awarded to each organization during the reporting period;
Page 1 of 2
