UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1218
1 and
2 (e) Any impacts or trends on juvenile delinquency rates, recidivism rates, and
3 detention numbers since the last reporting period.
4 (6) The General Assembly recognizes that expenditures on delinquency prevention,
5 wraparound services, reentry, and alternatives to detention reduce juvenile
6 delinquency, recidivism, and involvement in the adult justice system, and
7 therefore finds that:
8 (a) The fund established by this section should receive significant funding,
9 indicative of the Commonwealth's commitment to the future of our youths;
10 and
11 (b) The General Assembly should shift the funding priorities in juvenile justice
12 to reduce the incarceration of youths and increase the use of supportive
13 programming.
14 Section 2. There is hereby appropriated General Fund money in the amount of
15 $10,000,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 to the juvenile services fund created in Section 1 of
16 this Act.
17 Section 3. Whereas Kentucky has a paramount interest in reducing the number
18 of incarcerated youths, and the General Assembly is committed to ensuring transparency
19 and rigorous evaluation of investments to this end, an emergency is declared to exist, and
20 this Act takes effect on July 1, 2026.
